data.description: ARE YOU EXPERIENCING HIGH INTEREST RATE SHOCK?  CHECK OUT THIS LARGE BEAUTFUL HOME WITH A 2.5% ASSUMABLE LOAN *** TOTAL PAYMENT LESS THAN $2747/MONTH  *** LOW CLOSING COSTS *** 4.23 ACRES ***  NO HOA *** HORSE PADDOCK or GARDEN *** Welcome to this Historic Charmer - a turn of the century well maintained home on 4.23 acres that features large porches for entertaining, 10 foot ceilings, custom tile in kitchen and bath rooms, 6 Bedrooms, 3 Full Baths, 2 Half Baths, 3 staircases, transom windows over doors, library,  horse paddock, run in shed, tack room, equipment barn, gazebo, pool house and pool, plus original hardwood floors throughout the home. Better than New *** This is one of a kind and in EXCELLENT condition on 4+ acres of peaceful privacy.  This perfect location in a quiet rural Estate setting has previously been a successful Airbnb and could easily be used as a Wedding/Event Venue or enjoyed as a private residence. The large, mature trees are home to many varieties of birds that create a peaceful setting plus there is room for your horse, goats and chickens. Additional adjoining land available to lease if desired. ***************************************************************************************************************** The home conveys with a recent roof and siding and warranty on both. For added protection, the house has been under a termite prevention contract for many years. 4.23 acres for animals, gardens, and RV/truck/equipment parking with no HOA, covenants or restrictions !! NO HOA !!  This home is registered with the  Maryland Historic Registry, CH-218, but is not encumbered by any restrictions.  The home has Open Beams in the kitchen, Antique Decorative Moldings and Transom Windows throughout, Stainless Steel Appliances, large and mostly fenced yard, corner lot, rural views. Infrastructure is very sound with 2 gas/heat pump furnaces, 2 central air units, 400 amp electric, wired for generator, drilled well, underground electric, FIOS Internet. **********The property is located in the highly sought after school district of Dr. Thomas L. Higdon Elementary School, Piccowaxen Middle School and La Plata High School !! ***** Close proximity to Dahlgren, VA (11 miles), La Plata, MD (11 miles), Pax River (30 miles), Fredericksburg, VA (37 miles), Cove Point, MD (37 miles), Washington DC (38 miles), Alexandria, VA (39 miles). ***** Location History: The Town of Newport, Maryland Historic Registry, CH-786,  was established when settlers migrated from St. Mary's City in the late 1600's to the New Port. Historic artifacts have surfaced from that era (circa 1710 - 1870).  Agent has financial interest in property and is willing to help with closing costs.
